The two most popular hymns in this batch are <hymn>`hymn(1062)`</hymn> and <hymn>`hymn(1061)`</hymn>. The first one is explained because it's a Fast Sunday hymn so there's a good reason to sing it every month. The second was popular around [Father's Day](/posts/fathers_day) and [Mother's Day](/posts/mothers_day). While not apparent in this table, <hymn>Long Ago, Within a Garden (#1210)</hymn> was also somewhat popular around [Easter](/posts/easter). It was brand new then, so it didn't get sung much, but I suspect next year we'll see it sung more.  It's pretty cool to see new hymns being introduced in those categories since the number of hymns in each one of those is pretty small.

## What hymns are most popular each week?

This plot shows how popular each hymn is each week. Take these numbers with a grain of salt, particularly the left sides of each panel, because there's not a lot of data to work with. 


::: {.cell .column-page}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![](index_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-14-1.png){width=1248}
:::
:::



The clearest trend is the rise and fall of <hymn>Long Ago, Within a Garden (#1210)</hymn> around Easter. The other one is the regular spike in <hymn>Lord, Accept Our Humble Fast (#1062)</hymn> each month. We can also see <hymn>Love Will Bless Our Home (#1061)</hymn> spiking around Mother's Day and Father's Day. The other hymns don't show too clear of a pattern. 

